      "arraySize": 1,
      "dimensions": 1,
      "description": "chopop -  - Combine CHOPs combines the first channels of each , the second channels of each , etc.. Channels between inputs can be combined by number or name. Combining (Logic) Operations are:\n\n off - and - On if all inputs are on, otherwise off. or - On if at least one input is on, otherwise off. xor - On if one input on, but not more than one. nand - Off if all inputs are on, otherwise on. nor - Off if at least one input is on, otherwise on. eqv - On if inputs are equal (all on or off), otherwise off. lowest - Gives the lowest index of the channel that is currently on, or -1 if no channels are on. highest - Gives the highest index of the channel that is currently on on, or -1 if no channels are on.",
      "tooltip": "",
      "help": "",
      "units": "",
      "examples": [],
